<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR III" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. III" ;
	dprr:hasID 5 ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. III. Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR III" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR II" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II" ;
	dprr:hasID 2 ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II (99 B.C.-31 B.C.). Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR II" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8320> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8320" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "That these Legates continued in command for at least three years, and probably more, is indicated by the term of command of Gellius over his fleet (Cic. P. Red. ad Quir. 17, referring almost certainly to 63)." ;
	dprr:hasID 8320 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8319> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8319" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pompey's Legates in the war with the pirates (see 67, Legates) probably remained in their positions. L. Octavius may have substituted for the deceased L. Cornelius Sisenna." ;
	dprr:hasID 8319 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7976> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7976" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Leg., envoy 67. In MRR 2.147 and 149, refer also to Liv. Per. 99; Flor. 1.42.6. See Schleussner, Legaten 239, no. 234.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7976 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4807> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4807" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Other Legates appointed under the Gabinian and Manilian laws probably continued to serve under Pompey (see 67, and 66, Legates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4807 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4735> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4735" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Also a Legate, Envoy in the same year." ;
	dprr:hasID 4735 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4723> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4723" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "15 Under the Gabinian law Pompey was entitled to appoint Legates with praetorian imperium (App. Mith. 94; cf. SIG³ 750; Plut. Pomp. 26) to the number, according to Plutarch, of 15 (Pomp. 25; cf. Dio 36.37), according to Appian (Mith. 94), of 24; of that number we have the names of the 15 listed above, 13 of whom held command each in one of the 13 special areas designated by Pompey (see Zonar. 10.3). Their appointment may well have been extended in a number of cases with the extension of the term of Pompey's command under the Manilian law. At any rate Gellius was still in command of a fleet in 63 (Cic. P. Red. ad Quir. 17). See Mommsen, Str. 2.656, note 2; Th. Reinach, RPh 14 (1890) 150. On his Legates and plan of campaign, see P. Groebe, Klio 10 (1910) 374-389; H. A. Ormerod, Liverpool Annals of Art and Archaeology 10 (1923) 46-51." ;
	dprr:hasID 4723 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4722> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4722" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Under Cn. Pompeius Magnus against the pirates:" ;
	dprr:hasID 4722 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4713> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4713" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Pompey, who sent him to Crete to receive the surrender of the cities and oppose Metellus (Plut. Pomp. 29.2-5; Dio 36.18.1-19.1). See Legates, Lieutenants." ;
	dprr:hasID 4713 .
